  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AL-02 sensitivity gap)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across five flow-speed operating points, yielding 95th-percentile hemolysis index bounds that remain below the clinical threshold. A screening sensitivity study was conducted during model development to identify influential boundary-condition parameters; findings informed the UQ input distributions. All 13 credibility factors have been assessed and required levels are met or exceeded at MRL 5. Decision: Accepted.",
